  sugar: 30 g
  protein: 28 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 680 mg
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-corn-and-bacon-chowder-5c47846fc445fa62e95874c2
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 45 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and
dice @Yellow Onion{2}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites
from greens. Halve @Lemon{1}. Drain and rinse @Corn{13.4%ounce}.

Heat a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Bacon{4%ounce} and cook,
flipping, until crisp, ~{8-10%minutes}. Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate.
Place @Naan Bread{4} on a #baking sheet{}; drizzle with @Olive Oil{8.5%teaspoon}
and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Bake on top rack until crisp,
~{6-8%minutes}. Halve naan.

Melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onions
and scallion whites. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Season generously with salt and pepper. Stir in @Flour{2%tablespoon} and cook
~{1%minute}. Slowly pour in @Milk{13.5%ounce}, a little at a time, until
completely incorporated.

Stir potatoes, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2}, and @water{2 1/2%cups} into pot.
Season with plenty of pepper. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a
simmer. Cook until potatoes are tender and easily pierced by a knife, about
~{15%minutes}.

Once potatoes are tender, lightly mash in pot with a #potato masher{} until
chunky—some pieces should be crushed, but a few whole ones should still remain.
Stir in corn and allow to warm through. Stir in half the @Sour Cream{8%tablespoon}.
Taste and season with plenty of salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if soup is very thick.

Place @Mixed Greens{4%ounce} and @Dried Cranberries{2%ounce} in a
#large bowl{}. Add a squeeze or two of lemon juice and @Olive Oil{2 1/2%tablespoon}.
Season with salt and pepper; toss to combine. Crumble bacon. Divide soup
between bowls. Dollop with remaining sour cream. Sprinkle with
@Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup}, bacon, and scallion greens. Serve with naan for
dipping and salad on the side.